{"title":"sample package","content":"Package sample is a fixture exercising every ParseGodoc chunk shape:\npackage overview, exported funcs, exported types with methods and\nconstructors, const groups, and var groups. Used as a golden-file\nanchor for parse_test.go — keep this file deterministic."}
{"title":"sample.Hello","content":"Hello returns a polite greeting; it is a top-level package-scope\nfunc returning a builtin, so go/doc files it under Package.Funcs\n(not under any type).\n\nfunc Hello(name string) string"}
{"title":"sample.Config","content":"Config controls runtime behavior of the sample package.\n\ntype Config struct {\n\t// Verbose toggles chatty logging.\n\tVerbose bool\n}\n\n## Constructors\n\n### NewConfig\n\nfunc NewConfig() *Config\n\nNewConfig returns a default-initialized Config.\n\n\n## Methods\n\n### Apply\n\nfunc (c *Config) Apply(opts ...Option)\n\nApply mutates c per the supplied options."}
{"title":"sample.Option","content":"Option mutates a Config in place.\n\ntype Option func(*Config)\n\n## Constructors\n\n### WithVerbose\n\nfunc WithVerbose() Option\n\nWithVerbose returns an Option that enables verbose mode."}
{"title":"sample.MaxItems ...","content":"Operational limits exposed to callers.\n\nconst (\n\t// MaxItems caps the number of items per batch.\n\tMaxItems\t= 100\n\t// MaxRetries caps the per-request retry count.\n\tMaxRetries\t= 3\n)"}
{"title":"sample.Greeting","content":"Greeting is the canonical hello-world string.\n\nconst Greeting = \"hello\""}
{"title":"sample.Defaults","content":"Defaults is the Config used when nothing else applies.\n\nvar Defaults = Config{Verbose: false}"}
